I am extremely sorry to hear you lost your kitty to FIP. Nicole, I lost my kitten to FIP two Februaries ago, and then my adult kitty to the same disease a few months later, which is extremely rare for an adult to contract. I still cry about the loss of them to this day. I had both of them cremated and I have a little alter. My brother created a beautiful portrait of my kitten that I hung above. Little things we can do to honor their friendship and what good times we spent together. The good news is that they have found a cure for FIP. The bad news is that it will take long for it to be approved by the FDA. Most people don’t understand how tragic FIP is because they’ve only heard of FIV or other more common diseases. Watching your kitty have to battle FIP while knowing a cure is unavailable is something I wish on nobody. Sending all the love.
